  "text": "# SMARTSAVER ACCOUNT  \n**Q: What is the SmartSaver Account?**\nA: Our flagship savings account with competitive interest rates (4.50%–4.80%), no monthly fees, and easy access to your money anytime.  \n**Q: What interest rate will I earn?**\nA: Rates depend on your balance:\n- £0–£10,000: 4.50% AER\n- £10,001–£50,000: 4.70% AER\n- £50,001+: 4.80% AER  \n**Q: Is the interest rate fixed or variable?**\nA: Variable. Your rate adjusts monthly with the Bank of England base rate. We maintain a fixed 2.5% margin above BoE, so if BoE changes, your rate changes proportionally.  \n**Q: When is interest paid?**\nA: Monthly, on the last business day of each month. Interest is calculated daily.  \n**Q: What are the fees?**\nA: No monthly fees. Only optional fees:\n- International ATM withdrawal: £2.50\n- International transfer: £5.00\n- Card replacement: £15.00  \n**Q: Can I withdraw my money anytime?**\nA: Yes, anytime with no penalties or waiting periods. Easy access is a core feature.  \n**Q: What's the minimum opening balance?**\nA: Just £1. No minimum to open, no minimum to keep the account open.  \n**Q: Can I open a joint account?**\nA: Yes. Two customers can hold one SmartSaver Account together. Both have equal rights to withdraw.  \n**Q: How do I open an account?**\nA: Three ways:\n1. **Online:** www.firstuk.bank/open-account (1–2 days)\n2. **In Branch:** Visit any FirstUK location (same day)\n3. **By Post:** Call 0800-555-2265 to request pack (5–7 days)  \n**Q: What documents do I need?**\nA:\n- Photo ID (UK Passport or Driving License)\n- Proof of address (utility bill, council tax, or bank statement)  \n---",
